Interface Callback

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    IStream, StandardSession.FrameBytes
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AsyncMiddleManServlet.ProxyReader, AsyncMiddleManServlet.ProxyResponseListener, AsyncProxyServlet.StreamReader, BlockingCallback, BlockingWriteCallback.WriteBlocker, Callback.Adapter, CompletableCallback, CountingCallback, DeferredContentProvider, FutureCallback, FutureWriteCallback, Generator.Result, HttpContent, HttpInputOverHTTP, InputStreamContentProvider, IteratingCallback, IteratingNestedCallback, OutputStreamContentProvider, ProxyServlet.ProxyInputStreamContentProvider, SharedBlockingCallback.Blocker, StandardSession.CloseFrameBytes, StandardSession.ControlFrameBytes, StandardSession.DataFrameBytes, StandardStream, UpgradeConnection.SendUpgradeRequest, WriteCallbackWrapper

    public interface Callback

    A callback abstraction that handles completed/failed events of asynchronous operations.

    Semantically this is equivalent to an optimise Promise<Void>, but callback is a more meaningful name than EmptyPromise
